526968750

Justification (sketch): World population in 1800 ≈ 990,000,000. If the average human in 1800 spent about **2.1 minutes/day** actually *looking out through a window* (many had limited window access; most work was outdoors; but urban residents and those doing indoor tasks likely looked out more), then total human-days in the year are:

\[
990{,}000{,}000 \times 365 \times \frac{2.1}{1440}
= 526{,}968{,}750 \text{ days}
\]
